# Digital Literacy Project Report

## 1. Introduction
Digital literacy means having the skills to use digital devices, the internet, and online platforms in a safe and effective way. In today’s world, it is very important for students to understand how to use technology properly for learning, communication, and daily life.

This project helped me explore different aspects of digital literacy through practical tasks.

---

## 2. Objectives
- To understand the concept of digital literacy  
- To create and manage online profiles  
- To learn safe and responsible use of the internet  
- To improve communication skills through email writing  
- To understand cybercrime and its prevention  

---

## 3. Task Description

### Task 1: Presentation
In this task, I created a presentation on digital literacy using Canva. It included the meaning, importance, and uses of digital literacy in daily life. This task helped me improve my designing and presentation skills.

### Task 2: Portfolio
I created my profiles on LinkedIn and GitHub. I added my basic information, skills, and project details. This helped me understand how to maintain a professional online presence.

### Task 3: Platforms
I used platforms like Canva and Google Forms. I designed my presentation and also created a survey form related to digital literacy. This task improved my skills in using digital tools.

### Task 4: Email Etiquette
In this task, I learned how to write formal emails such as requesting an assignment extension and applying for an internship. I also understood the do’s and don’ts of using social media and email communication.

### Task 5: Cybercrime
I studied cybercrime and created a case study based on a real-life incident. I also included a prevention checklist to stay safe online. This helped me understand the risks of the digital world and how to avoid them.

